h%20the%20Indian%20government%20%26quot%3Bat%20the%20senior-most%20levels%26quot%3B%2C%20reported%20news%20agency%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20FT%20report%2C%20White%20House%20spokesperson%20Adrienne%20Watson%20said%20Indian%20counterparts%20had%20%26quot%3Bexpressed%20surprise%20and%20concern%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bstated%20that%20activity%20of%20this%20nature%20was%20not%20their%20policy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20understand%20the%20Indian%20government%20is%20further%20investigating%20this%20issue%20and%20will%20have%20more%20to%20say%20about%20it%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%20We%20have%20conveyed%20our%20expectation%20that%20anyone%20deemed%20responsible%20should%20be%20held%20accountable%2C%26quot%3B%20Reuters%20quoted%20her%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20un-named%20sources%2C%20Financial%20Times%20has%20reported%20that%20the%20US%20informed%20India%20about%20concerns%20regarding%20an%20alleged%20plot%20to%20kill%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20banned%20Sikhs%20for%20Justice%20(SFJ).%20The%20report%20said%20the%20US%20authorities%20also%20issued%20a%20warning%20to%20India%20over%20concerns%20the%20government%20in%20New%20Delhi%20was%20involved.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPannun%20is%20a%20dual%20citizen%20of%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20came%20two%20months%20after%20Canada%20said%20there%20were%20%26quot%3Bcredible%26quot%3B%20allegations%20linking%20Indian%20agents%20to%20the%20murder%20of%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20in%20June.%20India%20has%20rejected%20the%20allegations%20and%20sought%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20the%20anti-terror%20National%20Investigation%20agency%20filed%20a%20case%20against%20Pannun%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20issuing%20social%20media%20messages%20that%20said%20people%20flying%20with%20Air%20India%20were%20in%20danger.%20He%20had%20also%20claimed%20that%20A