0said%20that%20it%20left%20him%20disoriented.%20But%20then%20my%20father%20found%20the%20documents%20of%20sale%20that%20showed%20that%20the%20land%20had%20indeed%20been%20bought%2C%20back%20when%20he%20was%20a%20boy%2C%20from%20the%20family%20that%20was%20now%20claiming%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20286px)%2085vw%2C%20286px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22213006%2FScreenshot-2023-11-22-at-9.29.49-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22286%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22213006%2FScreenshot-2023-11-22-at-9.29.49-PM.png%20864w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22213006%2FScreenshot-2023-11-22-at-9.29.49-PM-229x300.png%20229w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22213006%2FScreenshot-2023-11-22-at-9.29.49-PM-783x1024.png%20783w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685976%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22374%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMy%20Son%20with%20Neo%2C%20Delhi%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20took%20my%20son%20on%20a%20walk%20to%20the%20village%20school%20that%20my%20father%20had%20built%20in%20my%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20memory.%20My%20father%20had%20been%20the%20first%20person%20in%20the%20entire%20district%20to%20be%20selected%20for%20the%20Indian%20Administrative%20Service%3B%20education%20had%20been%20his%20ticket%20out%20of%20the%20village.%20Most%20of%20his%20other%20relatives%20worked%20the%20land%3B%20a%20cousin%20became%20a%20doctor%20but%20others%2C%20if%20they%20left%20Jadopur%2C%20managed%20only%20to%20find%20low-paying%20jobs.%20When%20I%20was%20a%20child%2C%20my%20grandfather%20had%20been%20the%20village%20headman%2C%20but%20by%20the%20time%20I%20was%20in%20my%20teens%20power%20had%20shifted.%20My%20grandfather%20lost%20the%20panchayat%20election%20to%20a%20man%20from%20a%20lower%20caste.%20The%20family%20has%20little%20land%20remaining%2C%20but%20my%20father%2C%20perhaps%20because%20he%20feels%20he%20must%20give%20back%20what%20he%20owes%20to%20the%20land%2C%20has%20cultivated%20a%20philanthropic%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20school%2C%20boys%20were%20playing%20cricket.%20A%20middle-%20aged%20woman%20approached%20me.%20In%20a%20show%20of%20outdated%20modesty%20she%20had%20covered%20the%20lower%20part%20of%20her%20face%2C%20but%20I%20could%20see%20that%20she%20was%20smiling.%20She%20said%20that%20it%20was%20good%20I%20had%20come%20back%2C%20and%20then%2C%20pointing%20to%20a%20field%20close%20by%2C%20she%20said%20that%20a%20distant%20cousin%20of%20mine%20was%20now%20claiming%20that%20the%20land%20was%20his.%20I%20was%20taken%20aback.%20My%20relationship%20to%20the%20village%20was%20already%20tenuous%2C%20uncomfortably%20distant.%20Now%20it%20felt%20under%20threat.%20For%20decades%2C%20this%20land%20had%20been%20in%20the%20possession%20of%20my%20family.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%20to%20say.%20I%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20really%20back.%20I%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20in%20a%20position%20to%20do%20anything.%20I%20was%20just%20visiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20thought%20came%20to%20me%20again.%20When%20my%20father%20was%20gone%2C%20a%20large%20part%20of%20my%20past%20would%20disappear%2C%20like%20one%20of%20those%20videos%20you%20see%20of%20landslides%2C%20an%20entire%20cliff%20with%20a%20winding%20road%20and%20cars%20disappearing%20into%20the%20swirling%20river.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20land%20or%20property%20that%20I%20was%20thinking%20about%3B%20I%20was%20thinking%20about%20my%20parents%2C%20my%20mother%20who%20had%20come%20to%20this%20village%20as%20a%20young%20bride%2C%20and%20my%20father%2C%20who%20had%20brought%20me%20today%20to%20the%20place%20where%20he%20had%20been%20born.%20It%20was%20the%20people%20who%20had%20made%20my%20past%20who%20would%20soon%20be%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%20found%20me%20in%20quiet%20retreat%2C%20making%20a%20drawing%20of%20two%20adjacent%20mustard%20fields%20I%20had%20seen%20in%20the%20village.%20Is%20art%20a%20retreat%20from%20life%20and%20its%20contradictions%3F%20The%20answer%20would%20be%20yes.%20At%20least%20for%20me%2C%20that%20day.%20My%20eye%20had%20been%20attracted%20by%20the%20two%20intersecting%20lines%20of%20dense%20green%20topped%20by%20the%20bright%20yellow%20of%20the%20mustard%2C%20and%20now%20I%20felt%20compelled%20to%20render%20it%20all%20in%20a%20sombre%20monochrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20360px)%2085vw%2C%20360px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22213115%2FScreenshot-2023-11-22-at-9.31.01-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22213115%2FScreenshot-2023-11-22-at-9.31.01-PM.png%20864w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22213115%2FScreenshot-2023-11-22-at-9.31.01-PM-300x260.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685977%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22312%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMy%20Father%20with%20My%20Son%20Patna%2C%20Bihar%2C%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20remembered%20both%20sides%20of%20that%20dirt%20road%20from%20my%20childhood%2C%20and%20the%20endless%20fields%20that%20stretched%20beyond.%20It%20was%20all%20very%20peaceful.%20Difficult%20to%20imagine%2C%20while%20looking%20at%20the%20small%20parcels%20of%20land%20with%20their%20neat%20rows%20of%20crops%2C%20all%20the%20battles%20over%20property%20waged%20within%20families%20and%20communities.%20As%20generations%20change%2C%20the%20plots%20are%20divided%20among%20siblings%20and%20grow%20smaller.%20There%20is%20less%20and%20less%20left%20to%20share.%20People%20leave%20for%20the%20cities.%20New%20buyers%20take%20over.%20This%2C%20at%20least%2C%20is%20what%20has%20happened%20in%20my%20village.%20My%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20land%20was%20divided%20between%20my%20father%20and%20his%20two%20brothers%2C%20but%20none%20of%20them%20live%20in%20the%20village.%20One%20of%20my%20uncles%20sold%20nearly%20all%20his%20land%20and%20moved%20to%20Bengaluru.%20I%20cannot%20imagine%20my%20own%20family%E2%80%99s%20link%20to%20this%20rural%20place%20lasting%20beyond%20me.%20What%20I%20would%20like%20is%20for%20my%20father%20to%20sell%20his%20land%20during%20his%20lifetime%2C%20so%20that%20the%20new%20owners%20of%20the%20land%20will%20be%20from%20the%20village.%20Poorer%20families%20who%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20simply%20up%20and%20move%20away.%20But%20why%20was%20it%20so%20hard%20to%20tell%20him%20this%3F%20To%20bring%20up%20the%20question%20of%20land%2C%20of%20inheritance%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20my%20father%2C%20too%2C%20in%20a%20far%20more%20real%20way%20than%20me%2C%20experienced%20the%20loss%20of%20his%20past.%20And%20he%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20going%20to%20let%20it%20all%20disappear.%20He%20told%20me%20how%20he%20was%20a%20boy%20of%20eight%20or%20ten%20when%20he%20first%20saw%20an%20electric%20bulb.%20The%20world%2C%20and%20even%20his%20village%2C%20had%20changed%20so%20much%20during%20his%20long%20lifetime.%20He%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20going%20to%20let%20me%20talk%20him%20out%20of%20the%20bit%20of%20land%20that%20had%20been%20the%20one%20stable%20corner%20of%20his%20life%20since%20his%20childhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20were%20on%20our%20way%20back%20to%20Patna%20from%20the%20village%2C%20our%20car%20entered%20Motihari.%20This%20was%20the%20town%20where%20Gandhi%20had%20launched%20the%20satyagraha%20movement%20against%20the%20British.%20My%20son%20asked%20my%20father%20if%20he%20had%20memories%20of%20a%20childhood%20visit%20to%20Motihari.%20%E2%80%98Yes%2C%E2%80%99%20my%20father%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20came%20here%20in%201944%20to%20get%20my%20coat%20stitched.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20father%20began%20to%20tell%20my%20son%20that%20in%20the%20year%201892%2C%20his%20great-grandfather%20Bhikhari%20Kuer%20had%20come%20to%20Champaran%20from%20Saran.%20As%20my%20father%20talked%2C%20I%20began%20to%20take%20notes.%20Bhikhari%20Kuer%20had%20five%20sons.%20His%20youngest%20son%2C%20Shrikrishna%20Kuer%2C%20had%20three%20sons%2C%20the%20youngest%20of%20whom%2C%20Amar%20Kuer%2C%20was%20my%20grandfather.%20I%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20heard%20all%20the%20names%20of%20my%20ancestors%20that%20my%20father%20was%20reciting%20before%20now.%20Even%20as%20I%20was%20writing%20the%20names%20down%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20when%20my%20father%20was%20gone%2C%20no%20one%20would%20remember%20the%20details%20of%20our%20rural%20past.%20For%20my%20son%E2%80%99s%20children%2C%20or%20his%20grandchildren%2C%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20name%20and%2C%20in%20time%2C%20my%20own%20name%2C%20might%20well%20be%20as%20remote%20to%20their%20lives%20as%20the%20name%20of%20my%20great-%20grandfather%20had%20become%20to%20mine.%20This%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20good%20or%20a%20bad%20thing%3B%20it%20was%20the%20way%20time%20worked.%20It%20also%20meant%20that%20the%20face%20I%20had%20seen%20on%20all%20the%20billboards%20in%20Delhi%20and%20in%20other%20cities%E2%80%94at%20the%20petrol%20station%2C%20on%20billboards%20at%20each%20street%20corner%2C%20in%20offices%2C%20in%20ads%20and%20in%20reports%20in%20every%20newspaper%E2%80%94wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20around%20forever.%20And%20that%2C%20at%20least%2C%20gave%20me%20some%20comfort.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700703026000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22213352%2FScreenshot-2023-11-22-at-9.33.30-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Famitava-kumar-the-yellow-book%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20my%20father%20was%20gone%2C%20a%20large%20part%20of%20my%20past%20would%20disappear%2C%20like%20one%20of%20those%20videos%20you%20see%20of%20landslides%2C%20an%20entire%20cliff%20with%20a%20winding%20road%20and%20c